  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca.\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca. \u0d9a\u0dda\u0dad \u0dbd\u0db6\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "QR for business vehicles. Opportunity to get codes",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Vehicles owned by businesses enter the number of the registration certificate of the relevant business and ask through the National Fuel License. R. Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said that the code is available.",
        "The minister also mentioned that businesses with several vehicles were registered with the business registration number of all their vehicles."
